---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Our Way of Life — Ravings"
  description="The philosophy connecting poetry and OwOL — two expressions of living intentionally."
>
  <article class="page-owol">
    <header class="page-owol__header reveal" data-reveal="fade-up">
      <h1 class="page-owol__title">Our Way of Life</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="page-owol__body reveal" data-reveal="fade-up" data-reveal-delay="200">
      <p>
        Poetry and food are both acts of nourishment. One feeds the soul, the other the body.
        Both carry heritage, memory, and identity. Both are best when shared.
      </p>

      <p>
        <em>Ravings</em> is a collection born from the same impulse that drives
        <a href="https://owol.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">OwOL</a>
        &mdash; Our Way of Life &mdash; a desire to live with intention, to fight for what
        matters, and to gather around the things that sustain us.
      </p>

      <div class="author-card">
        <img
          src="/chidi-onwuka.jpg"
          alt="Chidi Francis Onwuka"
          class="author-card__photo"
          width="200"
          height="200"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <div class="author-card__info">
          <h2 class="author-card__name">Chidi Francis Onwuka</h2>
          <p class="author-card__role">Poet &amp; Builder</p>
          <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/chidi-onwuka"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="author-card__linkedin"
            aria-label="Chidi Onwuka on LinkedIn"
          >
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M20.447 20.452h-3.554v-5.569c0-1.328-.027-3.037-1.852-3.037-1.853 0-2.136 1.445-2.136 2.939v5.667H9.351V9h3.414v1.561h.046c.477-.9 1.637-1.85 3.37-1.85 3.601 0 4.267 2.37 4.267 5.455v6.286zM5.337 7.433a2.062 2.062 0 01-2.063-2.065 2.064 2.064 0 112.063 2.065zm1.782 13.019H3.555V9h3.564v11.452zM22.225 0H1.771C.792 0 0 .774 0 1.729v20.542C0 23.227.792 24 1.771 24h20.451C23.2 24 24 23.227 24 22.271V1.729C24 .774 23.2 0 22.222 0h.003z"/>
            </svg>
            <span>LinkedIn</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>
        Chidi writes about resilience, exile, heritage, and connection.
        His poems don&rsquo;t shy from darkness &mdash; they sit inside it and find
        what endures. From the defiance of <em>&ldquo;Still, We Fight&rdquo;</em> to the
        tenderness of <em>&ldquo;We Were All Strangers Once,&rdquo;</em> the collection
        maps the terrain of a life lived fully.
      </p>

      <h2>The Builder</h2>

      <p>
        OwOL is a food lifestyle app that brings the same philosophy to your kitchen.
        It&rsquo;s about more than recipes and grocery lists &mdash; it&rsquo;s about the
        dinner party you throw for friends, the recipe your grandmother never wrote down,
        the way a shared meal turns strangers into family.
      </p>

      <blockquote>
        <p>
          &ldquo;Hello&rdquo; is a soft incantation, that summons kindred flame.
          Suddenly, the spaces between are not absence, but invitation &mdash;
          not voids, but bridges arching across the unknown.
        </p>
      </blockquote>

      <p>
        Both the poetry and the app are expressions of the same question:
        <strong>What does it mean to live well?</strong>
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
